      • addAlbum

        public void addAlbum(Map<String,Object> params,
            ISirqulCallback<AlbumResponse> callback)
        Creates a new album.

        Target API Endpoint: /consumer/album/add

        Available parameters for this api
        • SirqulKeys.accountId of type Long
          the account ID of the user (deviceId or accountId required, deviceId added automatically)
        • SirqulKeys.title
          the title of the album
        • SirqulKeys.mediaFilePath
          the media file path containing the cover image of the album (this will also the image to the album itself)
        • SirqulKeys.assetId
          the asset ID to set the album cover image
        • SirqulKeys.attachedMediaFilePath
          the attached media file path containing an asset that the "media" file references. Example to upload a video: the "media" file should contain a screen capture of the video, and the "attachedMedia" should be the actual video.
        • SirqulKeys.attachedMediaURL
          this can be used if the "attachedMedia" is a link (i.e. a Youtube video, etc)
        • SirqulKeys.coverAssetNullable
          determines whether the cover image of the album can be empty, else will use the user's profile picture as the cover image
        • SirqulKeys.includeCoverInAssetList
          determines whether the cover image should be added to the album asset list
        • SirqulKeys.startDate
          the start date
        • SirqulKeys.endDate
          the end date
        • SirqulKeys.tags
          the tags
        • SirqulKeys.description
          the description of the album
        • SirqulKeys.albumType
          a custom field used for aggregation and searching
        • SirqulKeys.publicRead
          determines whether the album's participants has read permissions
        • SirqulKeys.publicWrite
          determines whether the album's participants has write permissions
        • SirqulKeys.publicDelete
          determines whether the album's participants has delete permissions
        • SirqulKeys.publicAdd
          determines whether the album's participants has add permissions
        • SirqulKeys.location of type Location
          the location used to update the album's location
        • SirqulKeys.locationDescription
          the location description
        • SirqulKeys.visibility
          determines the album's participants (PUBLIC - includes everyone in the system as a potential participant, PRIVATE - only considers people who have been invited as participants)
        • SirqulKeys.appKey of type String
          the application key used to identify the application. Maps to "gameType".
        • SirqulKeys.cellPhone
          the cell phone number
        • SirqulKeys.fullAddress
          the full address

        SirqulResponse subclass type:
        a AlbumResponse on valid response, or SirqulResponse with error message
        Parameters:
        params - the Map<String, Object> containing the parameters, both required and any optional ones you wish to send through to this api.
        callback - an optional ISirqulCallback instance that handles your response from this Sirqul API call. With this, API responses are automatically checked for validity or invalidity, whether it was null entirely, and to throw a SirqulException for any and all Exception's that may have occurred. Each of these cases are broken up into separate interface methods. If you foresee yourself needing to handle all cases, it's recommended you simply instantiate a new ISirqulCallback instance, which will force you to implement all methods. If you really only care about one or a few of them, you can use the SirqulCallback class, which you can optionally override any of those same interface methods. If you wish to ignore any response, simply pass in null for this.
        See Also:
        AlbumObject.addAlbum(...)

      • approveAlbum

        public void approveAlbum(Map<String,Object> params,
                ISirqulCallback<SirqulResponse> callback)
        Sets the approval status of an album. Only an approval status of APPROVED or FEATURED will be returned when searching for public content. Only someone with EXECUTIVE rights or rights to edit the application can approve/feature the content.

        Target API Endpoint: /consumer/album/approve

        Available parameters for this api
        • SirqulKeys.accountId of type Long
          The account ID of the user (deviceId or accountId required, deviceId sent automatically)
        • SirqulKeys.albumId
          The ID of the album
        • SirqulKeys.approvalStatus
          The approval status to set {PENDING, REJECTED, APPROVED, FEATURED}

        SirqulResponse subclass type:

        • SirqulKeys.descending

          the start index for pagination
        • SirqulKeys.limit
          the limit for pagination
        • SirqulKeys.dateCreated

        • SirqulKeys.location of type Location

        • SirqulKeys.range

      • searchAlbumsByDistance

        public void searchAlbumsByDistance(Map<String,Object> params,
                          ISirqulCallback<AlbumListResponse> callback)
        Searches on albums sorted by proximity (the distance the album is away from the user). The user's current location is required.

        Target API Endpoint: /consumer/album/distanceSearch

        Available parameters for this api
        • SirqulKeys.accountId of type Long
          the account ID of the user (deviceId or accountId required, deviceId added automatically)
        • SirqulKeys.ownerId
          search on albums that have been created by this account
        • SirqulKeys.keyword
          keyword search string
        • SirqulKeys.filters
          list of Enums.Ownership
        • SirqulKeys.albumTypes
          filter albums with this album type
        • SirqulKeys.start
          the start index for pagination
        • SirqulKeys.limit
          the limit for pagination
        • SirqulKeys.dateCreated
          filter on items that have been created before this date (time-stamp in milliseconds)
        • SirqulKeys.location of type Location
          the location of where the search is centered on
        • SirqulKeys.range
          the maximum range the album can be from the user
        • SirqulKeys.appKey of type String
          the application key. Maps to "gameType".

        SirqulResponse subclass type:
        AlbumListResponse on a valid response, SirqulResponse on an invalid response with error message
        Parameters:
        params - the Map<String, Object> containing the parameters, both required and any optional ones you wish to send through to this api.
